<en-note><div><b><font style="font-size: 36px;">Introduction to the Spring Beans</font></b></div><div><br/></div><div><b><font style="font-size: 24px;">Creating the Maven Project in Eclipse</font></b></div><div><span>    </span>We assume that you have installed the Maven plugin for Eclipse and it should be</div><div>available in the Installed software as “Maven Integration for Eclipse”.</div><div>Step 1: File -&gt; New -&gt; Maven -&gt; Maven Project</div><div>Step 2: Provide the GroupId and ArtifactId. Usually the GroupId is the package name and</div><div><span>    <span>    <span>    and the ArtifactId is a program name.</span></span></span><br/></div><div><span><span><span>             GroupId = ca.kasrhi.spring.beans</span></span></span></div><div><span><span><span><span>    <span>    <span>     ArtifactId = MyBeans</span></span></span><br/></span></span></span></div><div><span><span><span><span><span><span><br/></span></span></span></span></span></span></div><div><b><font style="font-size: 24px;">Setting Up the Spring JAR files.</font></b></div><div><span>    The Spring Framework is the collection of JAR files and its very confusing to get the dependentcies</span><br/></div><div><span>right. Years back the Spring had one package where everything we need was in one place.</span></div><div><span>This is the main reason why we want to use the Maven. The Maven will take care of dependencies </span></div><div><span>and versions.</span></div><div>For the basic Spring Framework we need the following JAR files:</div><div>org.springframework (spring-core, spring-beans and spring-context)</div><div>To get these files,double click the “pom.xml” and in the bottom click on “Dependency” tab.</div><div><br/></div><div><en-media hash="3180c3d3b94c6e6e1c4c7fb5c36c9b34" type="image/png"/><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>After adding the jar files, we should have the following in our Maven Dependencies folder:</div><div><br/></div><div><en-media hash="2c53993554d9a827e7ece8c83f7d8496" type="image/png"/></div><div><br/></div><div><b><font style="font-size: 24px;">What is a Spring Bean any way?</font></b></div><div>In a simple term the spring bean is a hook ( or wiring). </div><div>The beans  are Java obejcts like a POJO (Plain Old Java Object). As a matter of the fact,</div><div>we create the Java objects first and then we the beans to manipulate them.</div><div>Suppose we have a class called Cars.java. We create an instance of the class to use it:</div><div>Cars myCar = new Cars(); </div><div>Then we can access the properties and methods of the Cars cobject.</div><div>The Spring Framework allow us to create and manipulte the objects through the beans. The beans</div><div>act like an API to a class.</div><div><br/></div><div><b><font style="font-size: 24px;">Simple Example: <font color="#941100">The FibonacciNumbers.java</font></font></b></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;">public</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;">class</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> FibonacciNumbers {</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;"><span>    </span>public</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;">int</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> calculateFN(</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;">int</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">num</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">) {</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;"><span>    <span>    </span></span>int</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">a</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> = 1;</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;"><span>    <span>    </span></span>int</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">b</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> = 1;</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;"><span>    <span>    </span></span>for</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> (</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;">int</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">i</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> = 1; </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">i</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> &lt; </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">num</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">; </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">i</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">++) {</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;"><span>    <span>    </span></span>int</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">temp</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> = </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">a</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> + </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">b</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">;</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;"><span>    <span>    </span></span>a</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> = </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">b</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">;</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;"><span>    <span>    </span></span>b</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> = </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">temp</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">;</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"><span>    <span>    </span></span>}</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;"><span>    <span>    </span></span>return</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">b</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">;</span></div><div><span>    </span>  }</div><div>}</div><div><br/></div><div>The class has only one method “calculateFN” and no constructors ( except the default one).</div><div><br/></div><div><b>Step 1</b>: To use the Spring beans first we have to create the “Spring Bean Configuration File” .</div><div>             Click on the project name and<b> New</b> -&gt;<b> Other…</b> -&gt; <b>Spring</b> -&gt;<font color="#9437ff"> Spring Bean Configuration File</font>.</div><div>             Give a file<b><i> name</i></b> ( i.e. “<i>beans</i>”) and this will create a XML file ( <i>beans.xml</i>).</div><div><span>    <span>    <span>    <span> Note this configuration file can have as many beans as you want beans. In our case “Fibonacci Numbers”   </span></span></span></span></div><div><span><span><span><span>             will be </span></span></span></span>one of such bean.</div><div><span><span><b>Step 2:</b> Now we need to create a bean for our class. Double click on the bean’s XML (<b>beans.xml</b>). At the bottom </span></span></div><div><span>             there is the tab “beans”. We create by clicking “<b>New Bean..</b>”. Lets give an “<font color="#941100">id</font>” called “<font color="#0433ff">fibNum</font>” and then</span></div><div><span><span><span>             the class name “<font color="#0433ff">FibonacciNumbers</font>”. The beans XML file should look like this:</span></span></span></div><div><span><span><span><span><span>    <span>    <span>    <span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #009193;">&lt;?</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #4e9192;">xml</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #932192;">version</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">=</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #3933ff;">&quot;1.0&quot;</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #932192;">encoding</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">=</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #3933ff;">&quot;UTF-8&quot;</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #009193;">?&gt;</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #009193;"><span>    <span>    </span></span>&lt;</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #4e9192;">beans</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #932192;">xmlns</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">=</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #3933ff;">&quot;</span><a style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #3933ff;" href="http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans">http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans</a><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #3933ff;">&quot;</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #932192;"><span>    <span>    <span>    <span>    </span></span></span></span>xmlns:xsi</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">=</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #3933ff;">&quot;</span><a style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #3933ff;" href="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance</a><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #3933ff;">&quot;</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #932192;"><span>    <span>    <span>    <span>    </span></span></span></span>xsi:schemaLocation</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">=</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #3933ff;">&quot;</span><a style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #3933ff;" href="http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans">http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans</a>…&quot;<span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #009193;"/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Monaco; color: rgb(0, 145, 147);"><span>    <span>    </span></span>&lt;</span><span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Monaco; color: rgb(78, 145, 146);">bean</span><span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Monaco;"> </span><span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Monaco; color: rgb(147, 33, 146);">id</span><span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Monaco;">=</span><span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Monaco; color: rgb(57, 51, 255);">&quot;fibNum&quot;</span><span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Monaco;"> </span><span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Monaco; color: rgb(147, 33, 146);">class</span><span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Monaco;">=</span><span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Monaco; color: rgb(57, 51, 255);">&quot;ca.karshi.spring.Beans.FibonacciNumber&quot;</span><span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Monaco; color: rgb(0, 145, 147);">&gt;&lt;/</span><span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Monaco; color: rgb(78, 145, 146);">bean</span><span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Monaco; color: rgb(0, 145, 147);">&gt;</span><br/></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #009193;"/></div><div><span><span><span><span><span><span><span/></span></span><br/></span></span></span></span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #009193;"><span>    <span>    </span></span>&lt;/</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #4e9192;">beans</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #009193;">&gt;</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #009193;"/></div><div><br/></div><div>   <b> Step 3: </b>Once we have our bean ready, we can use it as follows in our <b>main</b> program:<br/></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;"><span>    </span>package</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> ca.karshi.spring.Beans;</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;"><span>    </span>import</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> org.springframework.context.ApplicationContext;</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;"><span>    </span>import</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> org.springframework.context.support.FileSystemXmlApplicationContext;</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;"><span>    </span>public</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;">class</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> App </span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"><span>    </span>{</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">    </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;">public</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;">static</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;">void</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> main( String[] </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">args</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> ) </span><span style="font-family: Monaco; font-size: 14px;">{</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">    </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #4e9072;">// Create the Spring beans container where the b</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #4e9072; text-decoration: underline;">eans</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #4e9072;"> reside </span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">    </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">ApplicationContext </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f; text-decoration: underline;">context</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> = </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;">new</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> FileSystemXmlApplicationContext(</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #3933ff;">&quot;beans.xml&quot;</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">);</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">    </span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">    </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #4e9072;">// Create the FibocanniNumbers </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #4e9072; text-decoration: underline;">instanace</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">    </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">FibonacciNumbers </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">FN</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> = (FibonacciNumbers) </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">context</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">.getBean(</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #3933ff;">&quot;fibNum&quot;</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">);</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">    </span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">    </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;">for</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> (</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;">int</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">num</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> = 0; </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">num</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> &lt; 10; </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">num</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">++) {</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">    <span>    </span></span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #931a68;">int</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">result</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> = </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">FN</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">.calculateFN(</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">num</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">);</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">        System.</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #0326cc;">out</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">.println( </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #3933ff;">&quot;Fibonacci Number for &quot;</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> + </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">num</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> + </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #3933ff;">&quot; is &quot;</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> + </span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #7e504f;">result</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> +</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco; color: #3933ff;">&quot;\n&quot;</span><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;"> );</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">        }</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">    }</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Monaco;">}</span></div><div><span>             </span></div><div><span>/*** The end of the Simple Example ***/</span></div><div><span><br/></span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>
